President Uhuru Kenyatta on Monday announced that all international flights shall resume from August 1. The President also announced the resumption of local flights from July 15 under strict guidelines in the country's planned phased reopening. The move comes after three months of suspension of all travels in and out of the country. "This will be in strict conformity with all protocols from the Ministry of Health, local as well as international civil aviation authorities and any additional requirements applicable at the ports of departure arrival or transit," he said. This comes after Kenya Airways sent home 182 pilots with more than 400 cabin crew facing job losses, raising questions over the future of the carrier. More to follow...